DOC.TE:
   Bush needs a carrot to hang out to Mexican President Vicente Fox;
at the same time he risks allowing potential terrorists to buy their
legal status. Is this a great country?

   Bubby's Restaurant & Pie Co., 120 Hudson St.; 219-0666;
www.bubbys.com. Lunch dishes $2-$10; brunch dishes $9-$16. Open daily
for breakfast and lunch (or brunch on weekends), daily for dinner.

   Nobu, 105 Hudson St. (at Franklin); 219-0500;
www.myriadrestaurantgroup.com. Appetizers and special dishes $6-$29;
three-course $20.02 lunch; dinner main courses $22-$27; omakase
(chef's choice menu) $80 and up per person. Open daily for dinner,
Monday-Friday for lunch. Next Door Nobu, at the same address, has the
same menu and prices but does not take reservations.

   Pico, 349 Greenwich St. (at Harrison); 343-0700;
